From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shadowy Super Coder <fullmetal@start9.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] riscv: dts: spacemit: enable BPI-F3 EEPROM on I2C2

The OpenWrt BPI-F3 image (target/linux/spacemit/image/k1-sbc.mk packages
DEVICE_DTS=k1-x_deb1) boots with the vendor deb1 DTB. The 6.18 vendor
DTS already declares the on-board GT24C02B EEPROM as eeprom@50 under
&i2c2 with compatible = "atmel,24c02", but ships it with
status = "disabled", so the at24 driver never binds despite the chip
being reachable at I2C bus 2, address 0x50.

Flip status to "okay" so the at24 driver exposes the chip at
/sys/bus/i2c/devices/2-0050/eeprom for the userspace ONIE-TLV read path
(StartWRT reads tag 0x2F as the WiFi PMK).

Signed-off-by: Shadowy Super Coder <fullmetal@start9.com>
---
 arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-x_deb1.dts | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-x_deb1.dts b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-x_deb1.dts
--- a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-x_deb1.dts
+++ b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-x_deb1.dts
@@ -1143,3 +1143,9 @@
 	pinctrl-0 = <&pinctrl_rpwm2_0>;
 	status = "okay";
 };
+
+&i2c2 {
+	eeprom@50 {
+		status = "okay";
+	};
+};
